The paper discusses the use of mutual information for variable selection in nonlinear modelling, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The data being analyzed is from spectrophotometers, which is a common tool in computer vision and image processing (cs.CV). The paper also mentions overfitting and generalization abilities, which are common concerns in neural networks and other forms of nonlinear modelling (cs.NE). Finally, the paper emphasizes the interpretability of the results, which is a topic often discussed in the field of social impact of AI (cs.SI).
